"Dichtdoen" is [[Dutch language|Dutch]] and means "to close", as in "Would you close the door? - Wil jij de deur dichtdoen?". "Sluiten" means the same thing. The word consists of 2 parts, as in: "I close the door. - Ik ''doe'' de deur ''dicht''." The word is based on "doen" or "to do" in English.


I close - Ik doe dicht
He closes - Hij doet dicht
We close - Wij doen dicht
I closed - I deed dicht
We closed - Wij deden dicht
We/I've closed - Wij/Ik heb(ben) dichtgedaan